Stop PieHelper (Quit to shell at CLI tools location):break
Configure PieHelper:confpieh_ph.sh -c
Unconfigure PieHelper:confpieh_ph.sh -u
Unconfigure and uninstall PieHelper:confpieh_ph.sh -s
List PieHelper configuration state and version:confpieh_ph.sh -g | more
List all available options for PieHelper:confopts_ph.sh -p list -a PieHelper | more
View the value of any PieHelper option(s) (Variable expansion disabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a PieHelper -g
View the value of any PieHelper option(s) (Variable expansion enabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a PieHelper -g -r
View/Change the value of read-write PieHelper option(s) (Variable expansion disabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a PieHelper -s
View/Change the value of read-write PieHelper option(s) (Variable expansion enabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a PieHelper -s -r
Set PieHelper options back to default:for i in PH_PIEH_PERSISTENT PH_PIEH_CMD_OPTS PH_PIEH_CIFS_SHARE PH_PIEH_CIFS_USER PH_PIEH_CIFS_PASS PH_PIEH_CIFS_SRV PH_PIEH_CIFS_DIR PH_PIEH_CIFS_SUBDIR PH_PIEH_CIFS_MPT PH_PIEH_PRE_CMD PH_PIEH_POST_CMD PH_PIEH_USE_CTRL PH_PIEH_NUM_CTRL;do; ph_set_option_to_default $i;done
Display help for PieHelper option(s) (Variable expansion disabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a PieHelper -d
Display help for PieHelper option(s) (Variable expansion enabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a PieHelper -d -r
Display TTY currently allocated to PieHelper:confapps_ph.sh -p tty -a PieHelper | more
Go to Main menu:ph_show_menu Main
Go to Apps menu:ph_show_menu Apps
Return to previous screen:return
